# ATS API — Minimum Request & Minimum Config Rules

## 1. Minimum headers per request

Use only the headers the API strictly requires. Start with `Content-Type: application/json` and nothing else. Do not add `cookie`, `authorization`, `x-requestverificationtoken`, `user-agent`, `referer`, or `origin` unless a 4xx response proves they are needed.

```python
# Correct
resp = requests.post(url, headers={"Content-Type": "application/json"}, json=body)

# Wrong — do not copy browser headers blindly
resp = requests.post(url, headers={"cookie": "...", "origin": "...", ...}, json=body)
```

## 2. Minimum config per client

Only store what **changes between clients** in `config/ats/<provider>/<client>.json`. Everything constant across all clients of the same provider belongs in code.

| Put in config file | Hardcode in `jobs.py` |
|--------------------|-----------------------|
| URL (differs per client) | Request body (same for all UKG clients) |
| Client-specific IDs | Common filters / pagination defaults |

UKG example — config file is just one line:
```json
{ "url": "https://recruiting2.ultipro.com/..." }
```

Current UKG convention in this project:
- URL stays in `config/ats/ukg/<client>.json`
- request body stays hardcoded in `src/ats/ukg/jobs.py`
- do not move short-lived tokens, cookies, or copied browser headers into config

## 3. Verify unauthenticated access first

Before adding any credential to config or `.env`, test the stripped request. Public ATS job boards are usually open APIs.

## 4. Ask minimum info when onboarding a new ATS client

When setting up a new ATS client, ask only for what is needed for that provider:
- **UKG**: only the `LoadSearchResults` URL (from the job board page source or network tab)
- No cookies, tokens, or browser session data needed

Document the minimum required fields in `config/ats/<provider>/example.json`.
